$$\cL(\varphi * \ell_s)(t)=\cL(\varphi)(t) \cL (\ell_s)(t)=\cL(\varphi) (2 \pi/t)^s.$$
Then for $s \in \mathbb C$ and $\varphi$ such that
$$\sum_{n \gg 0}\frac{a(n) \cL(\varphi )(2 \pi n)}{n^s}$$ converges absolutely we have,  in the notation of \cite{DLRR23}, 
$$L_f(\varphi * \ell_s)=\sum_{n \gg 0}a(n) \cL(\varphi * \ell_s)(2 \pi n)=\sum_{n \gg 0}\frac{a(n) \cL(\varphi )(2 \pi n)}{n^s}.$$
